# Thorium Portable for Windows

Run `THORIUM.cmd` from the extracted directory. The browser is stored under
`BIN` and its profile is stored under `USER_DATA`.

`THORIUM_SHELL.cmd` uses the version-specific `thorium_shell.exe` path verified
when the archive was created and stores its profile in
`USER_DATA\thorium_shell`. Both launchers accept additional command-line
arguments and URLs.

The launchers disable profile encryption and machine binding so the profile can
move between machines. This reduces local protection for cookies, passwords,
and other sensitive profile data. Do not use the portable launchers when
OS-bound credential protection is preferred.
